5:
I don't know about you, but being
here again kinda makes me nervous.
8:
I wonder why we've been called to
the Diviners' Commission in the first
place...
17:
P-pardon me, but could you please
catch it?
20:
Thank you very much.
...Now, return to whence you came.
25:
The rabbit... turned into a drawing?
Whoa... Was it always art?
30:
Oh, um... Yes, it's a power of mine to
bring art to life...
34:
My apologies for keeping you
waiting, everyone.
37:
Thank you for coming. Before we
begin, allow me to facilitate
introductions.
45:
O-okay... I am Kugui Nishikaze, one
of the Chair's subordinates. It's very
nice to meet you.
50: I am Stella. This is Alk and Light.
55: So... Why are we all here?
60:
Because of this. Have you heard of
the Yokai Encyclopedia?
63:
Yes, that's the book Inaho created
with Gramp Zigza, isn't it? The one
meant to introduce yokai to people...
66:
Indeed, through art do they intend
to show others the yokai of the world.
69:
Which brings me to the task at
hand... I'd like you all to involve
yourselves in the creation of its
second volume.
74:
...Mind if I ask why the Diviners'
Commission is so interested in an
encyclopedia?
79:
Well, um... The book contains traces
of magic...
82:
Magic that is tied to the undefined
nature of yokai.
83:
Picture a small goblin, for example. If
enough people grew overly fearful
of one, it could transform into a
mighty orc...
88:
So... you're afraid people will come
to fear the yokai in those pages,
warping them into more powerful,
dangerous creatures.
91:
Normally, a book wouldn't pose such
a risk... But the illustrations in this
one are too close to reality.
95:
I am inclined to agree. As you
witnessed earlier, Kugui knows a
thing or two about intermixing art
and reality.
97:
She's the one who originally brought
the problem to my attention, after
all. That is why I'd like her to serve as
editor for the second volume.
100:
In that case... I suppose our task is to
bring her to Inaho and Gramp Zigza.
103:
Kugui, now that introductions are
out of the way, you can return to
your room and prepare yourself for
travel.
106:
In truth, there is another reason why
I called for your assistance. Follow
me.
112:
Wow... These are so GOOD! Did Kugui
paint all of these?
116:
None of the subjects are depicted
with eyes.
121:
Once upon a time, Kugui's power
raged out of control in her home
village.
125:
Once the dust settled, her village
was abandoned, and she lost all
memories of her life before the
incident.
130:
The lack of eyes is a precaution,
then—against losing control of her
power once more?
134:
That is correct. She lives in fear of
her creations...
139:
Uh... Are you sure it's okay to send
her on this job?
142:
It's for this very reason that she's
only meant to become the editor
and nothing more.
145:
Still, I'm certain she'll have to paint
at some point.
148:
I realize I'm asking much of you
already, but could you watch over
her?
154: Of course. Leave her to us.
158:
All this art here proves that, deep
down, she still wants to create, yeah?
160:
I'm no artist, so I'm not sure how
much help I'll be, but I'll do whatever
I can to back her up!
165: ...I am in your debt. Thank you.
189:
Then you do not know of the
seventh showdown between all the
heroines to see who belongs with
Kusanagi... A true battle of
FRIENDSHIP is what it was!
192:
In order to understand and accept
each other, we must do the same!
201:
I think she's talking about that
manga she likes.
206:
Um... Correct me if I’m wrong, but...
she's a yokai, isn't she?
210:
Yep, a crazy one who mixes up
reality with fiction.
215:
Be quiet! You will face us now! Awa,
Hie, Mugi!
